      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "I like the idea of using specific types. But if we're going to change this, I think I would feel slightly better defining a `typedef Port` for this. What if we want to support a protocol in the future with 32-bit ports? I do not see this as likelyâ¦ my intuition is that things are moving to *one-endpoint-per-address* conceptually instead of portsâ¦ and yes the port as a concept is typical to current Internet protocols, where they're all 16 bits. But I guess it's clearer too to have a named type.\r\n\r\nAnyhow concept ACK.",
